############################################################ # PG Setup Code ############################################################ Context('Numeric'); $true = PopUp( ["?","True","False","Neither (not a statement)"], "True", ); $exists = RadioButtons( ["\(\exists x P(x)\) must be true.","\(\exists x P(x)\) must be false.","\(\exists x P(x)\) could be true or could be false."], "\(\exists x P(x)\) must be true.", # correct answer ); $forall = RadioButtons( ["\(\forall x P(x)\) must be true.","\(\forall x P(x)\) must be false.","\(\forall x P(x)\) could be true or could be false."], "\(\forall x P(x)\) could be true or could be false." # correct answer );
############################################################ # Body ############################################################
BEGIN_PGML Let [`P(x)`] be the predicate, "[`3x+1`] is even." a. Is [`P(5)`] true or false? [_]{$true}{5}
a. What, if anything, can you conclude about [`\exists x P(x)`] from the truth value of [`P(5)\text{?}`]
[@KeyboardInstructions('[_]{$exists}{5}')@]**
a. What, if anything, can you conclude about [`\forall x P(x)`] from the truth value of [`P(5)\text{?}`]
[@KeyboardInstructions('[_]{$forall}{5}')@]**
END_PGML
############################################################ # Solution ############################################################
BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION [`P(5)`] is the statement "[`3\cdot 5 + 1`] is even", which is true. Thus the statement [`\exists x P(x)`] is true (for example, 5 is such an [`x`]). However, we cannot tell anything about [`\forall x P(x)`] since we do not know the truth value of [`P(x)`] for _all_ elements of the domain of discourse. In this case, [`\forall x P(x)`] happens to be false (since [`P(4)`] is false, for example).
END_PGML_SOLUTION
